  <div
    id="how-it-works-modal"
    class="fixed inset-0 bg-primary/20 backdrop-blur-sm z-50 flex items-center justify-center p-4 transition-all duration-300 hidden"
  >
    <div
      class="bg-canvas rounded-2xl max-w-lg w-full p-6 border border-hairline shadow-modal flex flex-col gap-4 animate-scale-in max-h-[85vh] overflow-y-auto"
    >
      <div
        class="flex justify-between items-center pb-2 border-b border-hairline-soft"
      >
        <h3 class="font-display font-semibold text-lg text-primary">
          Aspect Ratio Guide
        </h3>
        <button
          type="button"
          id="close-modal-btn"
          class="text-stone hover:text-primary transition-all text-lg cursor-pointer"
        >
          ✕
        </button>
      </div>

      <div class="text-xs text-slate leading-relaxed flex flex-col gap-3">
        <p>
          An <strong>Aspect Ratio</strong> represents the proportional relationship
          between a shape's width and its height. It is written as two numbers separated
          by a colon (e.g. <code>16:9</code>).
        </p>

        <h4 class="font-bold text-primary mt-1">
          Logical vs. Physical Dimensions
        </h4>
        <p>
          Modern screens have high-density pixel layers (like Apple Retina or
          high-DPI panels).
          <strong>CSS Pixels</strong> represent logical layout grid points used to
          scale web layouts.
          <strong>Physical Pixels</strong> are the actual individual LEDs or subpixel
          hardware grids. Multiplying CSS dimensions by the <code
            >devicePixelRatio</code
          > gives the exact physical hardware output.
        </p>

        <h4 class="font-bold text-primary mt-1">GCD-Based Ratio Reduction</h4>
        <p>
          We simplify dimensions into exact aspect ratios using the greatest
          common divisor (GCD) formula. This produces clean integer ratios like <code
            >16:9</code
          > instead of floating-point approximations.
        </p>

        <h4 class="font-bold text-primary mt-1">
          Nearest Standard Ratio Matching
        </h4>
        <p>
          Since window boundaries can be uneven, exact ratios can be chaotic.
          Our matching engine compares your current shape's decimal aspect
          against standard display templates and highlights the closest visual
          match.
        </p>

        <h4 class="font-bold text-primary mt-1">Calculator Modes</h4>
        <ul class="list-disc pl-4 flex flex-col gap-1">
          <li>
            <strong>Live Viewport:</strong> Monitors your active browser window dimensions
            in real-time.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Custom Calculator:</strong> Solve unknown dimensions, scaling
            factors, or ratios.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Compare Ratios:</strong> Visual side-by-side comparison of two
            different ratios.
          </li>
        </ul>

        <h4 class="font-bold text-primary mt-1">PPI Calculator</h4>
        <p>
          Pixel-per-inch density measures the sharpness of a display. Enter a
          display diagonal in inches with a resolution to compute PPI.
          Generally, &gt;200 PPI is considered Retina/HiDPI quality.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="flex justify-end pt-2 border-t border-hairline-soft">
        <button
          type="button"
          id="modal-ok-btn"
          class="px-4 py-2 bg-primary text-canvas hover:bg-charcoal text-[11px] font-semibold rounded-full transition-all cursor-pointer"
        >
          Got it
        </button>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

